#PostYourWork
They only let me film quidditch back then

Super Bowl Arrivals - Doesn't seem like a big deal but it's honestly one of the most high pressure parts of the day for me because it's such a tone setter for how the rest of my gameday is going to go. 

Yes, it's a small simple, non-meaningful moment. Just players walking from the bus to their locker rooms. But when you only get one chance to get the shot, and you don't have the freedom to walk with players like in "nornal" games, it gets a little dicey sometimes with positioning and players walking in front of each other. 

Thankfully we had multiple LCCs covering this moment and we didn't miss anything crazy!! 

Shot on URSA G2 with a 17-120mm on a Benro HiHat and Manfrotto head.
